As long as I remember trees were my refuge & passion. After canning, my mom, Bernadette, tossed peach pits into a trench out the kitchen window, we soon had peach trees. My Dad, Marty, loved grafting trees with grafting wax; he soon had pears & apples growing on the same tree. Dad was a master beekeeper, My memories are of wonderful home grown fruit trees, organic food & nut trees. Is it a surprise that I’m drawn to encaustic & trees? I escaped into trees for solitude, reading, and observing nature while always looking up.
Sometimes the your path in the road is hard to navigate. But when your path becomes tedious, just look up and follow the lights that guide you.

wp:postmeta.wp:meta_value: This photo taken from the street shows an open- air, upper-level stair landing to an apartment on the Lower East Side of Manhattan. The image is a mute testament to one of the perils of big-city living, though I find the situation not without its humor, a point I hope is apparent from the title.
Reflected on the glass facade of a nearby office building, the Freedom Tower demonstrates the strength and resilience of the American spirit.
